Burglar (1987) Comedy, Caper, Action, 80&amp;#039;s Buddy-Cop, Whoopi Goldberg, Bob Goldthwait

Honeyko review: Once upon a time, before Whoopie got all annoying and politically-correct, she made a couple hep-cat comedy films, of which &quot;Burglar&quot; is the best. Great scenes involve her cop-proof apartment, and the motormouth Tourette Syndrome sufferer played by Goldthwait -- if you want raunchy ringtones, scavenge this movie for audio clips.

Source: eMule AVI of unknown origin; full-screen (no WS version has been released); 560x416 XviD, 117Kbps vbr mp3. I adjusted aspect ratio to 4x3 using MPEG4Modifier, and remuxed in AVImuxGUI to shave a few MB off file-size.

